  };
</code></pre>
async.series:<p><pre><code>  async.series([
    function1,
    function2
    ],
    // optional callback
    function(err, results){
      // results is now equal to [&#x27;one&#x27;, &#x27;two&#x27;]
    });
</code></pre>
<i>async</i> has a lot of functionality. You can use <i>wait.for</i> and <i>async</i> at the same time. They supply different functionality.<p>Example:<p><pre><code>  results = wait.for(async.map,[&#x27;file1&#x27;,&#x27;file2&#x27;,&#x27;file3&#x27;], fs.stat);</code></pre>

